Visual Suggestions 5

1.According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention millions of older adults fall every year. While one in four people fall, fewer than half tell their doctor. Falls are the most common causes of traumatic brain injury, but they can be prevented in older adults by removing tripping hazards, such as throw rugs and clutter.

2. No child is injury proof, but parents and caregivers can take steps to increase precautions against head injury in children by taking children to playground with shock absorbing materials on the ground.
3.Tobacco taxes are the most cost-effective way to reduce tobacco use and health care costs, especially among youth and low-income people, while increasing revenue in many countries.
4.Also companies can play a part in the reduction of the risk of second hand smoking by  implementing and enforce smoke free polices.
5.Life expectancy can be increased with simple steps and changes to nutrition and healthy lifestyle.                6.Advanced technology can also play a virtual role in the Improvement of global Life expectancy.
